The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Twenty20 meet from today

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Come Thursday morning (9 am) and you will witness Mohammed Kaif and others belting the leather around at the Calcutta Cricket and Football Club (CCFC) ground. Occasion: the second edition of The Telegraph Twenty20 cricket tournament. 

Members of the star-studded Indian Airlines line-up, which also features former India players such as Nikhil Chopra, Vijay Dahiya, Reetinder Singh Sodhi, will take on Lankan Masters to kick-start the four-day extravaganza. 

Though Kaif is yet to arrive (he was scheduled to land in the city on Wednesday evening), the Indian Airlines teams liaison officer maintained the UP batsman would be playing in the teams opening encounter from 9 am Thursday. 

Thursdays second match will be between defending champions Karnataka XI and Chemplast (from 12.30 pm). 

The biggest attraction of the meet is Virender Sehwag. The out-of-form Indian opener will don ONGC colours. According to a CCFC official, Sehwag will arrive before Friday. 

The winners will depart richer by Rs 1 lakh, while the runners-up will get Rs 60,000. 

Also, there will be individual prizes for Man of the Series (Rs 12,000) and Man of the Match (Rs 5,000). 

THE TEAMS 

Group A: Karnataka XI, CAB XI, Chemplast. 

 Group B: Indian Airlines, ONGC, Lankan Masters 




